# Template. Copy this to `ssh-authorized-key.pub` (gitignored) and put your real
# SSH *public* key(s) in it — one per line. configuration.nix reads that file at
# build time and authorizes these keys for the `prashantsinha` user.
#
# Get your public key on the machine you'll SSH FROM (your laptop):
#   cat ~/.ssh/id_ed25519.pub      # or ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub
# No key yet?  ssh-keygen -t ed25519
#
# Lines starting with '#' and blank lines are ignored.
ssh-ed25519 AAAA...replace-with-your-public-key... you@pc-machine
